text:
@anglophils645 
TOTALLY AGREE.  The actors in the original "Casablanca" were so unique that no reboot can ever duplicate or improve it.  Same thing with "Sabrina," which was pure junk.  Harrison looked like he was actually in pain making the whole thing.
The only remake that I thought completely outshined the original was "The Thing," starring Kurt Russell.  The incredible special effects, all done in real time (no CGI) made the original look like Sesame Street.  I also wish they would remake "Forbidden Planet" for the same reasons, but again, replacing the stars would be incredibly difficult, especially Anne Francis, my first screen crush.

@FindingGinaMarie Hi Judy its Jimmy again.
I was looking at what you mentioned about the Sahara Desert  tour and it looks amazing  and an absolute must do 
My first question is about the food because while I can eat anything my wife  is very fussy,  also while we are both still mobile  I am 70 and Steph is 67  would that present any problems.

@Jasonnn1234The referee decisions are final. 

Senegal 1-0 Morocco. 

I would be salty too if my team got wiped out this badly on home turf.

@BHA231 Vous utilisez ce qu'on appelle le "whataboutism" (ou l'art de détourner le sujet vers d'autres problèmes pour éviter de répondre sur le fond).
Vous mélangez trois dossiers très différents : la normalisation avec Israël, les présides de Ceuta et Melilla, et le Sahara.
Mélanger la souveraineté nationale avec les alliances stratégiques ou des dossiers coloniaux différents ne change pas la réalité du terrain : le plan d'autonomie est aujourd'hui la seule base de discussion sérieuse pour la communauté internationale. Le reste n'est que rhétorique.

@Britannica1 Oh, man. Bro... you were in my neighbourhood? If I knew I'd have invited you for a beer!
Btw, my neighbourhood - there where Celtic Manor was - is predominantly Muslim. Take that as more interesting info.
Also that sinkhole has been there since 2013. The walkway was put up in 2023... yeah...
